msg.content:
Based on my sources, the heads of state of the belligerents in the War of the Third Coalition were:

- Emperor Francis II of Austria
- Napoleon Bonaparte, First Consul of France (later Emperor Napoleon I)
- King George III of the United Kingdom
- Tsar Alexander I of Russia
- Khalid ibn Saud, Emir/Sultan of Nejd

Here are the dates of their deaths:

- Emperor Francis II died on March 2, 1835.
- Napoleon Bonaparte died on May 5, 1821.
- King George III died on January 29, 1820.
- Tsar Alexander I died on December 1, 1825.
- Khalid ibn Saud died in 1814.
